DESCRIPTION:Join us on Wednesday\, May 6\, from 4 - 7 PM at Whispering Vine - South Creek for a tasting featuring High-Scoring Chianti.\nTasting Fee: $30 per person (Buy a tasting bottle and your fee is refunded.)\nFeatured Wines:\n- Tenuta di Arceno Chianti Classico Riserva 2020 – Wine Spectator 94\, James Suckling 93\, #24 Wine Spectator Top 100 of 2023 – The 2020 Riserva opens with cypress\, black cherry\, vanilla and subtle spice\, then carries tart raspberry\, white pepper and orange peel on a bright\, structured finish.\n- Tenuta di Arceno Chianti Classico 2022 – James Suckling 92 – Ripe strawberry\, violet and subtle white pepper lead into raspberry\, white chocolate and vanilla bean\, all framed by fresh acidity and a warm spice finish.\n- Ruffino Riserva Ducale Chianti Classico Riserva 2021 – Wine Spectator 93\, James Suckling 92\, #17 Wine Spectator Top 100 of 2025 – A complex Chianti with violet\, cherry\, wild berry and plum notes layered with tobacco\, clove and a fresh eucalyptus lift\, finishing balanced and persistent.\n- Frescobaldi Tenuta Perano Chianti Classico 2021 – Wine Spectator 93\, Decanter 90\, Vinous 90 – Bright ruby and floral\, with cherry\, plum\, violet and wild rose notes moving into clove\, cardamom and a fresh balsamic edge over silky tannins.\nCome explore High-Scoring Chianti and find your favorite bottle. Buy a bottle from the tasting and your fee is refunded.
LOCATION:85 Foothill Rd Ste 1 Reno\, NV 89511
SUMMARY:High-Scoring Chianti Tasting
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR